#: ../../talk/chat.rst:82
msgid "Smart Picker"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:84
msgid "The smart picker makes it easier to insert links, files, or other content into your conversations. Just choose the type of content you want to insert (files, Talk conversations, Deck cards, GIFs, etc.). You can also type `/` in the chat input to open the selector."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:94
msgid "Replying to messages and more"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:96
msgid "You can reply to a message using the arrow that appears when you hover a message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:101
msgid "In the ``...`` menu you can also choose to reply privately. This will open a one-to-one conversation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:106
msgid "Here you can also create a direct link to the message or mark it unread so you will scroll back there next time you enter the chat. When it is a file, you can view the file in Files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:109
msgid "Silent messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:111
msgid "If you don't want to disturb anyone in the middle of the night, there is a silent mode for chatting. While it is enabled, other participants will not receive notifications from your messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:118
msgid "Scheduling messages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:120
msgid "If you want to send a message not right now, but at a specific time, you can schedule it. Just select the desired date and time in the quick actions next to the input field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:125
msgid "You can find all your scheduled messages by clicking on the clock icon next to the input field. There you can edit, reschedule or delete currently prepared messages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:131
msgid "Chat summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../talk/chat.rst:133
msgid "When AI assistant is enabled, a summary can be generated for a conversation if there are more than 100 unread messages. You can generate it by pressing the button that is visible in chat above the first unread messages."
msgstr ""
